Which configuration option is used within a systemd unit file to configure how to handlean out- of- memory killer?
A)  OOMSetting=
B)  OOM=
C)  OOMPolicy=
D)  OOMSignal=
C
C. Out- of- memory configuration is controlled by OOMPolicy within a service file or canbe set to a default value in a systemd configuration file. The other options are not valid.
